   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>CHAPTER FOUR THE DEFINITION OF THE SPIRIT 3 Scripture Reading: Exo 30:22-30; 2 Cor 1:21; 1 John 2:20, 27; Eph 1:13, 11, 14; 4:30b; 2 Cor 1:22; Gal 3:8, 14; John 3:5-6; Heb 2:10; Gal 4:6; Rom 8:14-16; 15:16; 8:26; Titus 3:5b; 2 Cor 5:17 OUTLINE In the New Testament the Spirit is: The compound anointing Spirit Exo 30:22-30: Compounded with the unique God, as the base, as the divinity of Christ, typified by the one hin of olive oil v. 24b.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>With God's Divine Trinity, typified by the three units of five hundred shekels of the spices vv.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>23-24a.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>With Christ's humanity, typified by the four kinds of spices.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>With Christ's death and its killing effectiveness, typified by myrrh and cinnamon v. 23a.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>With Christ's resurrection and its repelling power, typified by calamus and cassia vv.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>23b-24a.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>As an ointment for the anointing of all the things and persons related to the worship of God vv.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>25-30; 2 Cor 1:21; 1 John 2:20, 27.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>As the Holy Spirit to seal the believers of Christ Eph 1:13; 4:30b; 2 Cor 1:22a: To dispense the divine element of the processed Triune God into the believers and saturate them with it.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Transforming the believers into the inheritance of God Eph 1:11.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>As the sealing Spirit to be a pledge to the believers Eph 1:14; 2 Cor 1:22b: Guaranteeing God as the inheritance of the believers.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>Giving the believers a foretaste of God as their heritage.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>The blessing of the gospel Gal 3:8, 14: To regenerate the believers, begetting them as the many sons of God John 3:5-6; Heb 2:10.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>As the Spirit of the Son to cry "Abba, Father" in the believers' heart and to lead the believers to walk as the sons of God Gal 4:6; Rom 8:14-16.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>As the Spirit for the priesthood of the gospel to sanctify the believers Rom 15:16.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>To intercede for the believers Rom 8:26.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>To renew the believers, making them the new creation of God Titus 3:5b; 2 Cor 5:17.</S>
   </TEXT>
